Introduction

This confidence report is intended to help find places in the document which may not be tagged as desired. Add Tags uses general rules to identify document structure, and these rules may not produce the desired result in all cases. This report lists pages that you may want to check. Clicking on the any item will highlight the corresponding document element in the PDF. The TouchUp Reading Order tool can then be used to make changes in the tagging. There is also a hints section which describes how to make changes. The hints section also gives advice to reduce the need to update tags in future documents, and therefore reduce the amount of manual correction required. Add Tags cannot generate alternate text descriptions for Figures and form fields. All Figures are listed to make it easy to find them for the purpose of adding the AltText descriptions which may be required for accessibility. This report is temporary and cannot be saved or reloaded. Furthermore, links from the report to this PDF will no longer work if the file is resaved with a different name, or pages are added, replaced, or deleted before all errors have been corrected.

Hints for Repair

How To Fix Figure Tagging

A figure can consist of text, graphic elements, and images. Figures do not always have smooth boundary boxes or background highlights which would aid in defining that figure. Common problems include partial figures, falsely including extra elements (such as text) as part of a figure, merging of two or more figures into a single figure, or the splitting of a figure into two or more component figures. Correction merely involves a proper grouping of all of the required elements in a single structural element. Also, the addition of actual text, alternate text(required for accessibility), expansion text (for abbreviations), or titles may be done once the elements are properly identified. Use the TouchUp Reading Order tool to correct any problems.

Jak Ustawić Etykietę AltText

Etykieta AltText lub ActualText jest wymagana w formacie PDF. Przez wykorzystanie etykiety AltText (aby opisać wygląd) lub ActualText (aby określić tekst stricte) sprawiamy, że figura będzie posiadała jakąś formę zrozumiałego opisu. Podczas gdy figura może w niektórych przypadkach już zawierać etykietę ActualText (takich jak drop cap lub pogrubiony tekst), etykieta AltText nie może być automatycznie syntezowana i musi być przypisana ręcznie przez autora. Użyj Panelu Etykiet, aby dostarczyć tę dodatkową informację.
